  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). An uncertainty quantification campaign was conducted covering inlet flow rate variability, rotational speed tolerances, and fluid viscosity uncertainty across the five operating points; the UQ results informed the validation comparison and confirmed robustness of the relative hemolysis index predictions. Sensitivity rankings derived from the UQ campaign are discussed in the validation report narrative.",
