    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of pump-induced hemolysis to variations in component dimensions for a centrifugal blood pump used during cardiopulmonary bypass surgery. Model influence is MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect tolerance decision could impact clinical hemolysis levels). Model Risk Level 2.",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to identify worst-case operating conditions for hemolysis across 5 flow-speed combinations for a Class II CPB device. Results compared against predicate device hemolysis using relative hemolysis index (RH < 1 acceptance criterion).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "name": "COU1: Cardiopulmonary bypass use (Class II)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/hemolysis-index-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index validation against FDA pump experimental data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RHI) compared against experimental measurements at 5 flow-speed operating points. All RHI predictions satisfied RH < 1.0 acceptance criterion. The UQ campaign encompassing 128-sample Latin hypercube sampling confirmed that sensitivity to inlet boundary condition uncertainty was the dominant contributor to prediction variance, with coefficient of variation below 8% across all operating points. Validation error metrics: mean absolute error 0.042 RHI units, maximum error 0.091 RHI units."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/mesh-independence-study",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh independence and discretization error quantification",
      "description": "Three-level mesh refinement study (coarse 2.1M, medium 5.8M, fine 14.2M elements) using Richardson extrapolation. Grid convergence index (GCI) for hemolysis index: GCI_fine = 1.3%, GCI_medium = 4.7%. Asymptotic ratio 1.02 confirms grid convergence. Discretization uncertainty contribution to total UQ budget: 18%."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/turbulence-model-verification",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Turbulence model verification and code verification results",
      "description": "SST k-omega turbulence model verified against analytical Couette flow and lid-driven cavity benchmarks. Residual convergence to 1e-6 confirmed for all operating points. MMS verification passed with observed order of accuracy 1.94 (theoretical 2.0 for second-order scheme). Iterative convergence uncertainty estimated at 0.3% of hemolysis index prediction."
    }
  ],
